---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { rel, SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../../consts';
const description = 'Privacy policy for Table Talk: Conversation Cards by Dudley Development.';
---
<Base title="Privacy Policy · Table Talk: Conversation Cards" description={description} path="/privacy/table-talk">
  <main class="page">
    <div class="wrap" style="max-width:720px;">
      <a class="back" href={rel('/privacy/')}>← All privacy policies</a>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="updated">Table Talk: Conversation Cards · Last updated July 1, 2026</p>

      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <p>
        Table Talk is a free conversation-card app supported by ads. We do not run accounts,
        analytics, or trackers of our own, and we never see your personal information. The prompts
        are bundled in the app, bookmarks stay on your device, and the app works without an account
        or internet connection.
      </p>

      <h2>What stays on your device</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Your bookmarks and "Shuffle My Picks" deck.</li>
        <li>Your recent card/session history.</li>
        <li>Your app settings, including purchase/ads state where applicable.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This information is stored locally on your device. We do not receive it. Deleting the app
        removes local app data from your device.
      </p>

      <h2>Prompts and sharing</h2>
      <p>
        All prompt text is included with the app. When you share a card, Table Talk generates an image
        on your device and hands it to the standard iOS share sheet. The destination you choose, such as
        Messages or a social app, handles that share under its own privacy practices.
      </p>

      <h2>Advertising (Google AdMob)</h2>
      <p>
        The free version may show ads between card sessions. Ads are served by <strong>Google AdMob</strong>,
        a third-party advertising network. To serve and measure ads, Google may collect device information
        such as the advertising identifier, IP address, and coarse ad-interaction data. We do not receive,
        store, or link any of this to you.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>How Google uses this data is described in <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads">Google's advertising policy</a> and <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy">Google's privacy policy</a>.</li>
        <li>The optional Remove Ads purchase removes ads from the app.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        We do not knowingly collect any data from anyone, including children under 13. There are no accounts,
        profiles, or in-app messaging.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        If this policy ever changes materially, the new version will be posted at this URL with an updated date
        above. Continued use of the app after a change constitutes acceptance.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions? Email <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
